## 9. Implementation and Change Management

### 9.1 Rollout Communication Plan

| Audience | Channel | Message | Timing |
|---|---|---|---|
| Senior Management / Board | Briefing presentation | Strategic value of AI ethics framework; regulatory obligations | Before launch |
| Department Heads | Workshop session | Responsibilities, reporting requirements, practical examples | Week 1 |
| All Staff | Email + team meetings | Policy summary, training schedule, key dos and don'ts | Week 1-2 |
| IT / Security | Technical briefing | Monitoring tools, approved AI list, incident procedures | Week 1 |
| External stakeholders | Website update | AI transparency statement, customer-facing commitments | Week 2-4 |

### 9.2 Change Management Process

When updating this framework or introducing new AI tools:

1. **Propose** — Document the change, its rationale, and affected stakeholders
2. **Impact assess** — Evaluate regulatory, ethical, and operational impact
3. **Consult** — Engage affected departments and, where appropriate, external stakeholders
4. **Approve** — Obtain senior management sign-off for material changes
5. **Communicate** — Notify all affected staff with clear explanation of what changed and why
6. **Train** — Provide updated training where the change affects day-to-day AI use
7. **Monitor** — Track adoption and address implementation issues within 30 days

